# JavaScript Standards

## Avoid Nested Ternaries

Use clear conditionals instead of complex nested ternaries.

```typescript
// ❌ Bad
return isPolish ? (hasAccess ? thirdValue : fourthValue) : secondValue

// ✅ Good
if (isPolish) {
  return hasAccess ? thirdValue : fourthValue
}
return secondValue
```

## Use Constants for Magic Values

```typescript
// ❌ Bad
if (user.type === 4) { /* ... */ }
if (status === 'active') { /* ... */ }

// ✅ Good
const USER_TYPES = { GUEST: 4, ADMIN: 1 } as const
const STATUS = { ACTIVE: 'active', INACTIVE: 'inactive' } as const

if (user.type === USER_TYPES.GUEST) { /* ... */ }
```

## Parallel Async Operations

Use `Promise.all()` for independent async operations.

```typescript
// ❌ Bad — sequential when not needed
const services = await getServices()
const certificates = await getCertificates()

// ✅ Good — parallel
const [services, certificates] = await Promise.all([
  getServices(),
  getCertificates(),
])
```

## Imports

- Use `@/` path alias (mapped to `src/`), never relative `../../` paths
- Import order is handled by `@trivago/prettier-plugin-sort-imports` — don't reorder manually

```typescript
// ❌ Bad
import { Locale } from '../../config/i18n'

// ✅ Good
import { Locale } from '@/config/i18n'
```

## Early Returns

Prefer early returns over deep nesting.

```typescript
// ❌ Bad
function process(data: Data | null) {
  if (data) {
    if (data.isValid) {
      return transform(data)
    }
  }
  return null
}

// ✅ Good
function process(data: Data | null) {
  if (!data?.isValid) return null
  return transform(data)
}
```
